parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front End Vibration and Steering Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive vibration and steering issues can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to major injuries or deaths.
symptoms: vibration occurs at high speeds (60-75 mph)
vibration persists despite multiple tire replacements

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Battery Storage Design and Acid Leak
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the battery storage under the rear passenger seat can cause acid leaks, which can lead to toxic and flammable fumes, potentially causing fires or explosions.
The sudden stalling of the engine without warning can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds, and can lead to fatal consequences.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Battery Wire Chafing and Fire Risk
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The battery wires under the back seat can chafe due to motion, causing a fire risk, which can lead to vehicle damage, injury, or even fatalities.

The failure of the oil pan gasket can cause oil leaks, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potentially causing a fire or engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the oil pan gasket
oil drips or puddles under the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signal switch can cause the turn signals to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially when changing lanes or turning.
symptoms: turn signals are stuck in the "on" position
turn signals do not cancel after turning.
